headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times. Alabama U. S. Senator-Mr. Badger-Com. Stockton and the Navy Department-The Gardiner Commission.

docs.lead_paragraph: Hon. BENJAMIN FITZPATRICK has been appointed United States Senator from Alabama, to succeed Mr. KING. Mr. FITZPATRICK is expected to arrive here on Tuesday. Senator COOPER has returned, in better health. Mr. CLEMENS will be in his seat to-morrow.

byline.original: Special Dispatch to the New-York Daily Times:

docs.lead_paragraph: The Mail is through from New-Orleans. The papers contain one day later from Mexico. No determination has been arrived at in regard to the Tehuantepac question. The Siglio contains a communication from the associates of Col SLOO, dcaying the accusation that their propositions require the cession by the Government of transit dues, and asserting that these will always remain a source of revenue to the Government.

docs.lead_paragraph: TEXAS ITEMS.--by the arrival of the steamship Texas, Capt. LAWRENCE, we have received Galveston papers to the 31st ult., one day later than those brought by the Mexico. The following is from the News: On Tuesday evening last Dr. GRANT, whose residence is near Washington, on the Brazos, was shot in Houston by Mr. ANSELEM HUDSON, who was acting as barkeeper in the Houston House.

docs.lead_paragraph: " Marriage is honorable," saith the Scripture, "and profitable for the state," say all wise men who eschew Malthus and his atrocities. A married man has motives to honorable exertions and for living wisely, that bachelors cannot find.
